<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-05-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-05-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="420" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d420">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 702.6211/231.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">German Ambassador</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">German Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-05-21">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 21, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary of State</hi>: I have the honor to
                            acknowledge receipt of your kind note, No. 1428, of the 18th instant. I
                            am gratified to learn therefrom that the authorities of the State of
                            Washington have now acknowledged as unfounded the charge against
                            Imperial Consul Müller and Secretary Schulz and have dismissed the
                            case.</p>
                        <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">J. Bernstorff</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>